{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T06:56:24.423Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kaiming initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") is a weight initialization strategy specifically designed for neural networks using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU-family activations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (ReLU, Leaky ReLU, etc.). It keeps activation variance stable across layers by using a variance scaled only by the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "number of input connections"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (fan-in), compensating for ReLU's tendency to kill half the activations."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "He Initialization — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What He Initialization Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Developed by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kaiming He"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (and colleagues) in 2015, He initialization addresses a key problem: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU discards negative inputs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (outputs 0), causing activation variance to shrink quickly across layers. He initialization uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "larger variance than Xavier"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to compensate."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Name"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Origin"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "From author \"Kaiming He\""}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kaiming"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Also called this (from paper title)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Matters: The ReLU Problem"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How ReLU Breaks Standard Initialization"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ReLU(x) = max(0, x)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Consequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - 50% of activations become "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (negative inputs)\n- Only 50% of neurons are \"active\" at initialization\n- With standard initialization (like Xavier), activation variance "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "shrinks exponentially"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across layers"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Signals vanish → gradients disappear → training fails in deep networks."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "He's Solution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "He initialization "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "compensates"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by using larger variance:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(W) = \\frac{2}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vs. Xavier's:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(W) = \\frac{2}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} + n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\\text{out}}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The factor of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "2"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (instead of balancing fan-in and fan-out) maintains variance despite ReLU killing half the inputs."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How He Works: The Formulas"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a layer with "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{in}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " input neurons (fan-in):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He Normal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nW \\sim \\mathcal{N}\\left(0, \\ \\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}}}}\\right)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He Uniform"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nW \\sim \\mathcal{U}\\left(-\\sqrt{\\frac{6}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}}}}, \\ \\sqrt{\\frac{6}{n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\\text{in}}}}\\right)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key differences from Xavier"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n| Property | He | Xavier |\n|----------|-----|--------|\n| "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " | "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " | "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}} + n_{\\text{out}}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " |\n| "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uses fan-out?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |\n| "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Factor"}, {"type": "text", "text": " | 2 in numerator | 2 in numerator |\n| "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Magnitude"}, {"type": "text", "text": " | "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Larger"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (weights ~1.4× bigger) | Smaller |"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why the Formula Works: Derivation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assumptions"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU activation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{ReLU}(x) = \\max(0, x)"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weights centered at "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (mean = 0)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weights are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "IID"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (independent and identically distributed)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Biases initialized as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "zeros"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivation"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a linear layer: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z = Wx"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Activation variance without ReLU:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(z) = n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} \\cdot \\text{Var}(W) \\cdot \\text{Var}(x)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "With ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", only 50% of inputs pass through:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(\\text{ReLU}(z)) = \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} \\cdot \\text{Var}(W) \\cdot \\text{Var}(x)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "To keep "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Var}(\\text{ReLU}(z)) = \\text{Var}(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", we need:\n\\[\n\\frac{1}{2} \\cdot n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}} \\cdot \\text{Var}(W) = 1\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solving for variance:\n\\[\n\\text{Var}(W) = \\frac{2}{n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{\\text{in}}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "factor of 2"}, {"type": "text", "text": " compensates for ReLU killing half the activations."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use He Initialization"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Component"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommendation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Activation function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Leaky ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (all ReLU-family)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fully connected"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convolutional"}, {"type": "text", "text": " layers (especially CNNs)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sigmoid"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "tanh"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier/Glorot"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why not Sigmoid/tanh?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " They're symmetric (output both positive and negative), so no need to compensate for dying activations → Xavier is better."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn.init as init\n\n# He Normal (default for ReLU in many cases)\ninit.kaiming_normal_(layer.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='relu')\n\n# He Uniform\ninit.kaiming_uniform_(layer.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='relu')\n\n# For Leaky ReLU (need to specify gain)\ninit.kaiming_normal_(layer.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='leaky_relu')"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Note"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "mode='fan_in'"}, {"type": "text", "text": " means using only "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{in}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (not "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{out}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ")."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow.keras.initializers as init\n\n# He Normal\ninitializer = init.HeNormal()\n\n# He Uniform\ninitializer = init.HeUniform()\n\n# Use in layer\nmodel.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, kernel_initializer=initializer, activation='relu'))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual Implementation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef he_init(n_in, n_out, scale=1.0):\n    variance = scale * 2.0 / n_in\n    return np.random.randn(n_in, n_out) * np.sqrt(variance)\n\n# Example: layer with 784 inputs, 128 outputs\nW = he_init(784, 128)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "He vs. Xavier Comparison"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "He Initialization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Xavier/Glorot"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance formula"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}} + n_{\\text{out}}}"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Activation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ReLU, Leaky ReLU"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sigmoid, tanh"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight magnitude"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Larger"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (more active neurons)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smaller (balanced)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why it works"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compensates for 50% dying activations"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keeps variance constant for symmetric activations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Default in"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern CNNs, ResNets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Legacy networks, old TF versions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fan-out used?"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quick rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sigmoid/tanh"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Numerical Example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Suppose a layer has "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{in}} = 100"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " input units:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He Normal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Variance: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{100} = 0.02"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Standard deviation: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sqrt{0.02} \\approx 0.141"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Weights: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{N}(0, 0.141)"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier Normal"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (assuming "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n_{\\text{out}} = 100"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " too):\n- Variance: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{100 + 100} = 0.01"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Standard deviation: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sqrt{0.01} = 0.1"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Weights: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{N}(0, 0.1)"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": He produces weights that are ~1.4× larger (0.141 / 0.1), keeping more neurons active."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of He initialization as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "\"volume boost for ReLU\""}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU"}, {"type": "text", "text": " kills half the signal (negative → 0)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Perfect volume for symmetric activations (tanh/sigmoid)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Boosts volume by 40% to compensate for ReLU's signal loss"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without this boost, signals get progressively quieter through layers → vanish → training fails."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "He initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is designed for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ReLU-family activations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to prevent vanishing variance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Normal "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{N}(0, \\sqrt{\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}})"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " or Uniform "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{U}(-\\sqrt{\\frac{6}{n_{\\text{in}}}}, \\sqrt{\\dots})"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{2}{n_{\\text{in}}}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " — uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "only fan-in"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (not fan-out)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Factor of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "2"}, {"type": "text", "text": " compensates for ReLU killing 50% of activations"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": ReLU, Leaky ReLU, PReLU, convolutional layers, CNNs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sigmoid/tanh (use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Xavier"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weights are larger"}, {"type": "text", "text": " than Xavier (~1.4×) → keeps more neurons active"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common default in modern frameworks for ReLU layers (PyTorch's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "KaimingNormal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", TF's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "HeNormal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "He initialization is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "standard for modern deep learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because ReLU is the dominant activation function in CNNs and deep architectures. Without it, training deep ReLU networks would be unstable or fail entirely."}]}]}}